On March 27th our good friend and Jackson Hole skier @bryce.newcomb3 took a fall in the Jackson Hole backcounty when a cornice broke under him. Bryce suffered a severe head injury and was air lifted to a nearby hospital. He is currently in the ICU and remains in critical condition. A Go Fund Me has been started to help cover medical bills that go beyond his insurance. Follow the link in our bio to learn more and support Bryce. Our thoughts are with Bryce and his family for a healthy recovery.

Meet avalanche dog Sable, a Boykin Spaniel. Medium sized and compact to carry, at 32 pounds, she is friendly, has an enthusiastic personality and is very lovable. Her large, feathery ears hang close to the cheeks, setting off an expression of soulful intelligence. Boykin Spaniels move with the effortless and balanced gait typical of durable gundogs. Bred to work in their native South Carolina, web-toed Boykins can swim like seals, and dig efficiently in the snow. She’s an avid worker, and we are proud to have her on our team. Powered by @nulopetfood. #jacksonhole #jhdreaming #avalanchedogs #nulodog #sponsored 📷 @amyjimmerson
